Putin Ally May Buy $2 Billion Fertilizer Plant, Vedomosti Says

-- B y  
-- 
2011-07-28T04:44:21Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-28/putin-ally-may-buy-2-billion-fertilizer-plant-vedomosti-says.html
Arkady Rotenberg, a judo partner of
Russian Prime Minister  Vladimir Putin , and his brother Boris
Rotenberg may buy nitrogen fertilizer maker  OAO Minudobreniya 
for $2 billion, Vedomosti  reported , citing unidentified people
familiar with the matter.  Ukrainian billionaire Dmitry Firtash gained control of
Rossosh, outbidding Russian companies OAO Acron and EuroChem,
the Moscow-based newspaper said. 